<p>It is often computationally unfeasible to have a small enough threshold. This would prohibitively decrease the acceptance rate in Markov chain Monte Carlo (MCMC) or sequential Monte Carlo (SMC) algorithms. Here, instead of a binary in-or-out comparison, we used a probability function proportional to the 
 <italic>χ</italic>
 <sup>2</sup> distance between simulated and observed data, 
